   <refnamediv>
       <refname>filter_like </refname>
               <refpurpose>Kalman filter log-likelihood </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[llik]=filter_like(param,func,y,x,F,z)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> param </term> =    a vector of parameters (sqrt of variances)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> func </term> =    the function which transforms the parameters into the matrix of variances (Q and R)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> y </term> =    (nx1) data vector</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =    (nxk) data matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> F </term> =    transition matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> z </term> =    (nxl) data matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
<listitem><para>*  <term> llik </term> =    - 2*log-likehood (+n*log(2*%pi))</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Generates model loglikelihood in a kalman model:
y(t) = X(t)*B(t) + Z(t)*A  + e(t), e(t) = N(0,R)
B(t) = F*B(t-1) + v(t),    v(t) = N(0,Q)
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// Filter_like is used by the function kalman:
oresult = maxlik(filter_like,grocer_param,grocer_func,grocer_y,grocer_x,grocer_F, varargin(:))
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
